Anthony Joshua has said he put on a masterclass, after regaining his world titles against Ruiz Jr. Ruiz shocked the boxing world, when he stopped Joshua in seven rounds on June 1 in New York. But the Mexican-American handed back the IBF, WBA and WBO heavyweight world titles in a unanimous decision, when they met for a second time in the Diriyah Arena, Saudi Arabia. Joshua told Sky Sports: “I respect Andy and his trainer so much. I wanted to show the sweet science of this lovely sport. “Stay hungry, stay humble. I’m humble in defeat and will stay humble in victory. “Careers are all about experience, I took my loss and bounced back, anyone can do it. You want me to retire and give up?” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.